<P>
   BOND-LOSSES (New York) _ While stocks have bounced, bonds, with
the exception of U.S. Treasury securities, have barely budged.
August, one of the most brutal months on record in almost every
bond market around the world, has been followed by a September in
which most of these securities, if they are up, have mustered only
the merest of gains. By Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
