   RATE-CUT-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ American investors seemed to
shrug off the news Wednesday that there appears to be no immediate
global interest rate cut in store to help calm world financial
markets. But that reaction should not be a surprise, because
according to one guage of investor sentiment, investors had been
shifting their view all week, betting that it is more likeley now
that there will not be any immediate action. By Jonathan
Fuerbringer.
