<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLANOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A TIME TO LASSO TEXANS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA's two-season, three-city Texas tour continues
Saturday in Houston, giving the Bruins another opportunity to show
their stuff for the top high school talent in the Lone Star State.
</P>
<P>
   Victories last year in Austin (over Texas) and Dallas (over
Texas A&AMP;M) provided UCLA critical exposure in its successful
pursuit of defensive tackle Sean Phillips and guard Steve Morgan.
</P>
<P>
   ``It sends a message to kids that they don't have to stay in
state just because it's Texas,'' said Phillips, a Parade
All-American from Dulles High in Sugar Land, a Houston suburb.
</P>
<P>
   ``For an out-of-state school, it gives them influence to get
kids to play for them. You can go judge for yourself if it's a good
team and if you want to play for them. It helps a lot, because
there are a lot of great players in Texas.''
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins lured Tommy Maddox, Kevin Williams and Skip Hicks out
of Texas in the past decade, and they've recruiting several players
this year, including two from Dulles: receiver Leroy Price and
linebacker Damian West, an elite national recruit.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's an opportunity for the players we recruit not only to see
us against the home team but to see us in person,'' said Randy
Taylor, UCLA's director of football operations. ``You can see the
uniforms, the size of the players, the offense.
</P>
<P>
   ``I believe the games in Texas helped us sign (Phillips and
Morgan). It's good to schedule games in areas you recruit.''
</P>
<P>
   Slippery when wet: The Bruins are expecting heat and rain at
Houston's 20,500-seat Robertson Stadium. But coach Bob Toledo will
not practice with wet footballs to prepare the quarterbacks and
receivers for adverse conditions.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's overrated _ I've ruined more practices with wet
balls,'' Toledo said. ``It's like, `Let's practice in the snow to
get ready for it.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Injury update: Second-string tailback Keith Brown left practice
early with turf toe and is day-to-day. If he can't play, true
freshman DeShaun Foster moves up the depth chart.
</P>
<P>
   Starting outside linebacker Michael Wiley injured his back and
also is questionable. Redshirt freshman Santi Hall, impressive
against Texas with a sack and three tackles, is ready if Wiley
can't play.
</P>
<P>
   Odds and ends: UCLA's 584 yards against Texas was its highest
output since November 1994, when the Bruins gained a school-record
679 yards against Arizona State....
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins scored touchdowns on all five trips inside the red
zone (20-yard line) against Texas....
</P>
<P>
   Guard Andy Meyers and tight end Ryan Neufeld were named captains
for the week, joining Cade McNown and Larry Atkins, the season-long
selections....
</P>
<P>
   Saturday's game will be broadcast on KOGO 600-AM because of a
conflict with the Dodgers on 1150-AM.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
