<HEADLINE>
MORTON EXPECTED TO MISS START
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Tailback Chad Morton probably will not start
against Oregon State after straining his back doing leg squats
earlier this week, USC coach Paul Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Morton will play, but Petros Papadakis is expected to start and
true freshman Frank Strong will also get increased playing time.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he'll be fine. He's been lifting the building. He
doesn't need to be on ESPN lifting barrels,'' Hackett said. ``He
just strained his back. I'm not concerned.''
</P>
<P>
   Morton hurt his back while lifting Monday, which is a
traditional no-practice day for the Trojans. He had missed
Tuesday's practice, but said it was because he didn't feel well.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you don't practice you don't get the opportunity to be a
starter,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Morton's reduced role could be a plus for Strong, who has taken
an increased number of snaps in practice this week.
</P>
<P>
   ``The coaches have told me, `You're just gonna have a few more
carries. Be ready,' '' Strong said.
</P>
<P>
   Strong is still excited about his college debut last weekend,
when he had three carries for 11 yards against San Diego State.
</P>
<P>
   ``Man, it was great. Just the time of my life. What I've been
waiting for,'' Strong said.
</P>
<P>
   Center of controversy: Starter Matt McShane has a twisted
ligament in his left knee, and is expected to miss the Oregon State
game. Eric Denmon, who started against Purdue, is out with a
sprained ankle. McShane will not need surgery, however, and it is
possible he could play against Florida State.
</P>
<P>
   ``It didn't hurt that much,'' McShane said. ``I limped off the
field but there wasn't a lot of pain. I just hit the ground.''
</P>
<P>
   David Pratchard and Jason Grain split time playing center in
practice Wednesday, although reserve Donta Kendrick is also a
possibility.
</P>
<P>
   ``We didn't have too many fumbles in practice today,'' Hackett
said. ``(Tuesday) was a disaster.''
</P>
<P>
   USC did get some good injury news. Linebacker Mark Cusano
(sprained left ankle) was cleared to practice Wednesday and strong
safety Grant Pearsall is practicing and will play.
</P>
<P>
   Early appearance for Palmer?: Mike Van Raaphorst will start
again at quarterback, but Hackett said he may try freshman Carson
Palmer in the second quarter of the Oregon State game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel good about him. He's gonna play better the more he
plays. Maybe the end of the second quarter this week,'' Hackett
said.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, Hackett said the same thing last week and Palmer
didn't enter the game until late in the third quarter.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
