Atlanta Journal when baseball was the Crackers in Ponce de Leon
Park, recently retired from airline consulting in Washington.
Christian wonders if anyone in the new Delta rides the mail truck
in New York, or hands out orchids in the afternoon; or if a
reservations agent in Florida loves his company so much he lists
Delta as his middle name in the telephone book. Of course not. We
all live in a different world in 1998. (Minter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
