</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   SCANDINAVIA _ OSLO, Norway _ On balance, we visit Scandinavia
for the pretty scenery and the pretty people. Yet Scandinavia
deserves an extended stay. Because these countries were spared the
full brunt of modern wars, their physical pasts remain remarkably
intact. Thus, the culturally curious visitor should make special
efforts to visit some small historical or art museums in the cities
of Oslo, Bergen, Stockholm and Copenhagen. (Barnes, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CALIFORNIA _ SAN FRANCISCO _ The descriptive term
``breathtaking'' is overused. Admit it, we all hate it. The canopy
of trees was breathtaking. Her beauty was breathtaking. The new
Mazda is breathtaking. Nonetheless, I'm traveling north on the
Pacific Coast Highway through Big Sur and I can't think of any
other word to describe the cragged cliffs, the crushing sea as it
meets the rocks. (Kallenberg, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MONTREAL _ Montreal offers a pleasant mix of European and
American sensibilities and features. With its museums, first-class
shops and ethnic neighborhoods, it does resemble a cleaner, smaller
New York. And because of its French heritage and largely
French-speaking population, Montreal does have a European flair.
(Breyer/Seaborn, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-YOGA _ NASSAU, Bahamas _ The boom of a gong pierced the
silence of the night promptly at 5:30 a.m., which is mighty early
on Paradise Island. This is the time to go to bed after a night at
the casinos and bars, not to get up to meditate and to do yoga
positions that turn your body into a pretzel. Do people really want
to do this on vacation? (Blackerby, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TRAILSEND _ TRAIL'S END, Minn. _ It's clear paddling into the
Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness that the name refers to more
than just the border between the United States and Canada. This is
the boundary line past which superfluous things like money and cars
and TV Guide don't matter _ or even are usable. Of course, a light
canoe helps in that quest, as we found out the hard way.
(Riemenschneider, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KINGSVILLE-TX _ The getaway just keeps getting better, as the
Youngs take B-Bar-B in Kingsville, Texas, from its beginnings as a
hunting lodge into a year-round resort stop for hunters, birders,
tourists and adults just wanting to hide out in comfort for a few
days. (Leggett, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   PHYSICAL-EXAMS _ The annual physical has become more than just
checking for blood pressure and heart condition. There is a growing
list of tests directed at a specific age. When should one have a
colon screen? What about the frequency of complete blood workups
and what does ``complete'' mean. (Martin, Austin
American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   DNA-OLDSLAYING _ AUSTIN, Texas _ This week's arrest of a suspect
in a murder many years old is being hailed as a testament to the
wonders of DNA testing. Yet this week's arrest also is the
culmination of a tale of two detectives, Parkinson, now a
lieutenant, and Sgt. Paul Johnson, who wouldn't let go of the case
even as Woods played games with the minds and emotions of
investigators. (Copelin, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
