<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUNBIZ-DEBUT-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BUSINESS EDITORS, WIRE EDITORS, NEWS EDITORS: 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   On Sunday, Sept. 20, The New York Times will introduce a
revamped Money and Business section that includes 32 standing
features or columns as well as a full-page graphics package on
stocks, interest rates, funds, currencies and commodities. The NYT
News Service will move the material each Friday for Sunday
publication.
</P>
<P>
   The inaugural SUNBIZ-ADVISORY will move today. All periodic
features, whether weekly, rotating or occasional, can be easily
identified by the standing KEYWORDS in their slugs, as indicated
below:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WEEKLY FEATURES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-WATCH _ The existing Market Watch column on a timely
topic from the financial world.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-PROFILE: A 1,000-word profile of an important and
interesting person in business or economic life. Slugs will take
the following form: BIZ-PROFILE-NAME (for example _
BIZ-PROFILE-GATES).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-BRIEFS: A column of short items on the people and
personalities that make business more than a dollars and cents
proposition.
</P>
<P>
   IN-MY: A 250-word voyeuristic feature that lets readers see
business personalities in more dimensions than they're usually
portrayed. Each week, the IN-MY- will be followed by a different
keyword _ IN-MY-LAPTOP, IN-MY-WALLET. The Sept. 20 inaugural piece,
IN-MY-BRIEFCASE, focuses on Harvard economist Jeffrey Sachs.
</P>
<P>
   ECON-COLUMN _ A weekly economics column with a rotating stable
of top business reporters including Louis Uchitelle, David E.
Sanger and Sylvia Nasar.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-COLUMN _ On alternating weeks, we will bring you a column
by Jonathan Fuerbringer on global markets and non-equity investing,
and another on investing strategies by Mark Hulbert, editor of the
Hulbert Investment Digest.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-WITH: A profile of a top mutual fund, hedge fund or
institutional money manager to see how a smart investor is
investing. Slugs will take the form: INVEST-WITH-NAME (i.e.,
INVEST-WITH-GREENSPAN).
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-DIARY: Short items about surveys, research, interesting
or suspect new financial products, etc.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-INSIGHT-Q&AMP;A: A forward-looking question-and-answer
session with a market insider.
</P>
<P>
   WORKING-COLUMN: A weekly look at one reader's career, workplace
or management dilemma and the reporter's best stab at resolving it.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-DIARY: Another venue for short items on studies, surveys,
goofy or splendid new consumer products, etc. These diaries can
appear in as many as four places each week _ in the PRIVATE SECTOR,
BUSINESS, INVESTING and/or PERSONAL BUSINESS areas of the
redesigned section. Slugs will take the form: BIZ-DIARY-INVEST.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-PRELUDES, BIZ-MIDSTREAM, BIZ-SENIORITY: These three columns,
which will focus on the different stages of financial life
(BIZ-PRELUDES _ getting started; BIZ-MIDSTREAM _ the prime earning
years; BIZ-SENIORITY _ prepping for retirement), will appear in
rotation once a month. On the one or two weeks a month when these
columns don't appear, BIZ-MYLIFE (an outside contributor's essay on
life colliding with money), will appear.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MONTHLY FEATURES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-BOOKS _ Deborah Stead's existing Off the Shelf
business-books column.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-JOBS _ Lawrence Van Gelder's existing jobs column.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-ETHICS _ An essay on real-life ethical dilemmas of workers,
managers and executives.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-CULTURE _ An essay on how business is portrayed in the
media.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OCCASIONAL FEATURES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-SMARTGIVING _ Stories labeled Smart Giving will focus on
philanthropy.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-VALUE _ Value for Money stories examine how to get top value
when purchasing goods and services.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-CONSUMPTION _ The Vicarious Consumption label goes on
features about the life-styles of the rich and famous.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-20-QUESTIONS _ Examples: 20 questions on leasing a car; 20
questions on buying a vacation time-share.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-5-QUESTIONS _ Five questions posed to an executive about a
deal, new strategy or business development.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-FIRST-JOB _ My First Job offers vignettes of how people of
accomplishment got started.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-MOMENTS _ Unguarded Moments offer vignettes from a business
person on the worst advice given or received, the worst day on the
job, etc.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-FOR-ME _ Working for Me features look at the world of
self-employed people.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-MANAGEMENT _ Conversational pieces on managerial
problem-solving and business issues are labeled Talking Management.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-BENCHMARKS _ Benchmarks are features on companies and
individuals that demonstrate top business practices.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-CONFLICT _ Under the banner of Man vs. Corporation or
Corporation vs. Man, these stories look at conflicts in the work
place.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-WRONG _ The Market Is Wrong features contrary-minded
stock and fund stories.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-SELL _ Stories on stocks and funds you may want to sell
are labeled Sell Signals.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-IPO _ At the Gate stories discuss initial public
offerings.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-INSIDERS _ Stories labeled Inside Track address the
trading activities of company insiders.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TEXT QUESTIONS: (888) 346-9867 &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Arceanious Felton (e-mail, felton(at)nytimes.com).
</P>
<P>
   Tim Hilchey, (e-mail, hilchey(at)nytimes.com).
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (888) 346-9867
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GRAPHICS: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   For a preview of the full page of graphics offerings, contact:
</P>
<P>
   Photo-Graphics editor Deborah Marchand
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (888) 603-1036
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: marchand(at)nytimes.com
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service.
</P>
