</P>
<P>
   Q. What is impeachment?
</P>
<P>
   A. It is an official accusation by the House of wrongdoing so
serious that if the official doesn't resign, the Senate must hold a
trial to decide whether he or she should be removed from office.
</P>
<P>
   Q. Who can be impeached?
</P>
<P>
   A. Any high federal official in the executive or judicial
branches of the federal government. The Constitution says, ``The
