<SLUG> BC-FBC-ASU-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SNYDER INSERTS BAKER AS KICKER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. - On the heels of Arizona State's second straight
loss, Coach  &UR; Bruce Snyder made his first personnel change
Wednesday, naming punter  &UR; Stephen Baker as the field-goal kicker
for Saturday's game with North Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Baker replaces redshirt freshman  &UR; Mike Gauthier, who made only
one of four field goals in the Sun Devils' two games.
</P>
<P>
   ``I still think Mike Gauthier could be a fine Division I
kicker,'' Snyder said. ``I just think we need to make a change
right now. I hate doing the same thing over and over if it's not
working.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think one of the definitions of insanity is keep doing the
same thing over and over, thinking you're going to get a different
result. I'm not insane, I don't think.''
</P>
<P>
   Snyder typically doesn't like one player to punt and place kick.
</P>
<P>
   Gauthier missed field goals of 44 and 30 yards against Brigham
Young. He made and missed 42-yarders against Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Keeping it simple &QL; 
Snyder's back-to-basics approach this week includes making life
simpler for the defense, which returns only three full-time
starters from last season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I really think it's important we don't have a lot of checks,''
he said. ``We've got to get into the flow of the game, go hit some
people and clean up tackles and gang tackle and strip the ball.
It's better than thinking, `What adjustment is this, what
adjustment is that.' We're trying to make it a little easier,
intellectually speaking.''
</P>
<P>
   Among the defensive newcomers who improved from the first to
second game was junior college transfer  &UR; Junior Ioane, defensive
coordinator  &UR; Phil Snow said. &QL; 
Getting tough &QL; 
Practices have been noticeably more intense this week. Snyder is
keeping a close eye on how his players react, because he is a
strong believer that the effort during the week reflects how the
team plays Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ``We got after them pretty good, and they didn't fight back,''
he said. ``They took it. In order to salvage and be back where they
can be, they've got to work harder. We're going to work them hard,
treat them like dogs if we have to.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have certain standards to how we should play, regardless of
who we're playing against. . . . We didn't have that against BYU. I
don't care who's coming in, what matters is how hard we play.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
