<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROENICK ADDS BULK FOR SEASON 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SCOTTSDALE, Ariz. - Assistant captain  &UR; Jeremy Roenick hopes this
will be a season of increases and one thing has already increased:
Jeremy Roenick _ there is a lot more of him.
</P>
<P>
   After undergoing a rigorous off-season weight lifting and
conditioning program in southern California, Roenick reported to
the Coyotes' training camp at 206 pounds, the heaviest of his
10-year NHL career.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've come in at 197 before, but it was usually more fat than
muscle,'' said Roenick, who looks significantly bigger in the chest
and shoulders, but thinks the new muscle went elsewhere. ``I'm a
lot stronger in my butt and legs. Just my luck, the last place
where I need an extra chunk is on my butt.''
</P>
<P>
   Roenick, who has three times scored more than 100 points in a
season and has twice scored 50 or more goals, has been taken to
task consistently in national hockey publications for falling
production. The 56 points he scored last year was the lowest he's
had in a full season since 1989-90, his first full year in the NHL.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't listen to that garbage anymore,'' he said. ``I've
worked hard to put myself in the best condition possible to have a
good season with weight training and by working on the (stationary)
bike. I should be much stronger this year.'' &QL; 
Missing member &QL; 
Wing  &UR; Dallas Drake missed Tuesday's scrimmage because of minor back
spasms. He's expected to play in tonight's Black and White
scrimmage at 7 p.m. at the Cellular One Ice Den.
</P>
<P>
   The scrimmage is open to the public, but team officials warn
only 200 seats are available and parking is negligible. &QL; 
New guy &QL; 
With  &UR; Mike Gartner in retirement, wing  &UR; Rick Tocchet has taken back
No. 22, which was worn the past two years by the fast-skating
Gartner. An onlooker joked to General Manager  &UR; Bobby Smith on
Tuesday that ``Gartner seems to have lost a step.''
</P>
<P>
   Smith answered, ``Maybe, but he's playing a lot tougher.'' &QL; 
Team effort &QL; 
Center  &UR; Cliff Ronning believes it unfair to expect one or two
players to pick up the scoring load that will be missed if Captain
 &UR; Keith Tkachuk's demand to renegotiate the remaining two years of
his contract keeps him out for the year.
</P>
<P>
   ``That situation is tough for everybody,'' Ronning said. ``Right
now we have to hold things together and not key on just one guy
having to score or this guy doing that. It has to be a team effort.
We win or lose as a team and that has to be the attitude all year.
If we play hard together, good things will happen.''
</P>
<P>
   FYI, Tkachuk's fines for missing camp soared past $50,000
Tuesday. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
