A0536 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BOOK-TAPE-SEMATARY-$A     09-17 0593
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BOOK-TAPE-SEMATARY-$ADV20-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AUDIO BOOKS: `PET SEMATARY' OFFERS AN EARFUL OF ACTION 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For release Sunday, Sept. 20)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By DOUG BLACKBURN  
 c.1998 Albany Times Union  
 _____  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (``Pet Sematary,'' by Stephen King. A fully dramatized
multivoice presentation by the British Broadcast Corp. Abridged,
approximately three hours. Simon &AMP; Schuster Audio. $18)
</P>
<P>
   Most books are read by a single actor, or, on rare occasions, by
the author. Which is why ``Pet Sematary'' is unique and a treat in
the world of audio books. This is a fully dramatized multivoice
presentation performed by the BBC and now reissued by Simon &AMP;
Schuster Audio.
</P>
<P>
   While plot is the real ruler in best-selling author Stephen
King's thrillers, sound effects and the voices of more than a dozen
talented readers make ``Pet Sematary'' crackle with tension it
would not have otherwise. Even children age 10 and up, who have
been exposed to some of the tamer horror movies, will be entranced
by this audio book, thanks mostly to the unique presentation.
</P>
<P>
   Like many of King's books, ``Pet Sematary'' is set in rural
Maine, where a young doctor has relocated his family in order to
raise their children in a tranquil place. But a pet burial ground
located near their home makes life anything but peaceful for the
Creed family. Listener, beware, and listeners, be advised: If fully
dramatized, multivoice presentations are the next wave for audio
books, it will be a fun ride.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _____ &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (``Power Plays Politika,'' created by Tom Clancy and Martin
Greenberg. Read by Jay O. Sanders. Abridged, approximately three
hours. Simon &AMP; Schuster Audio. $18)
</P>
<P>
   Tom Clancy fans, and they are many, should be warned.
``Politika'' is not a novel, per se, but a novel based on the Red
Storm Entertainment computer game in which Clancy is a creative
partner. The giveaway is on the box containing the two audio
cassettes: Clancy is listed as the creator, not the author.
</P>
<P>
   Read by the actor Jay O. Sanders (``Tucker: A Man and his
Dream'' and ``Glory,'' among other films), who smoothly alters his
voice to capture various Russian politicos as well as Americans,
``Politika'' is a thriller set on the cusp of the millennium.
</P>
<P>
   The pace is quick, the action decisive, the descriptions
surprisingly well written. But the men and women are caricatures,
devoid of complexity. This is what happens, I suppose, when you try
and breathe life into characters whose existence begins in a
computer game.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _____ &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (``Bloodstream,'' by Tess Gerritsen. Read by Jan Maxwell.
Abridged, approximately three hours. Simon &AMP; Schuster Audio. $18)
</P>
<P>
   Internist-turned-thriller-writer Tess Gerritsen has cashed in _
in a way the medical establishment never would have permitted _
with two best-sellers: ``Harvest'' and ``Life Support.''
</P>
<P>
   She has found a formula that works and is determined to pump it
for all it's worth. ``Bloodstream'' is her third book in three
years.
</P>
<P>
   A murderous epidemic has broken out in Tranquility, Maine, where
Dr. Claire Eliot has moved with her teen-age son. Eliot feels
compelled to uncover the epidemic's bizarre medical cause, no
matter how evil its roots.
</P>
<P>
   Unfortunately, Gerritsen's plot is so far-fetched and her
characters so poorly developed that her success as a writer is a
sorry indicator of how far the book-buying public's standards have
sunk. If quality was the determining factor, Gerritsen might well
be on the phone as we speak, contacting health care companies for
per diem work.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
