guitarist Lenny Kaye's seminal examination of the first generation
of punk, first issued by Elektra in 1972 and squeezed onto Disc 1
of ``Nuggets: Original Artyfacts From the First Psychedelic Era
(1965-68). Along with the original double-album, this entertaining
118-track, four-CD box offers a wealth of obscure singles and
pungent examples of '60s garage punk from regional scenes
throughout the country. By Fred Shuster. 
. 
