not cash the down payment check for him. He had only $400 in his
checking account.
</P>
<P>
   Traore does mostly small jobs for homeowners. ``From A to Z _
the house,'' he boasts. Most months, he grosses about $2,500, from
which he must buy materials and tools and support his wife and two
children, ages 2 and 7.
</P>
<P>
   When the check-cashing store clerk handed him his down payment
money, it was minus the store's $120 fee.
</P>
<P>
   ``Too much,'' he muttered. ``Too much.''
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
