House said it would veto the bill because it violates President
Clinton's call to set aside projected surpluses until the nation
comes up with a plan to shore up social security. By Richard W.
Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
   RACE-REPORT (Washington) _ After more than 15 months of work,
the Advisory Board on Race has produced a breathtakingly modest
report whose major recommendation is that President Clinton
institutionalize efforts to promote a dialogue on race by
establishing a Presidential council on race. By Steven A. Holmes.
</P>
