<P>
   HKN-PANTHERS-DVORAK _ SUNRISE, Fla. _ The Florida Panthers'
coaches and scouts didn't know what to make of Radek Dvorak at his
first training camp in 1995. The Panthers' first-round pick (and
10th overall) that year, Dvorak beat everyone in the 5-mile run,
then stayed a step ahead of the competition the rest of the week,
leading the team with six goals in five scrimmages. Unfortunately,
three years later, that remains the highlight of Dvorak's NHL
career _ that and the five-game point streak he put together to
close last season. (Biggaine, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
