   FBN-COWBOYS-GARRETT _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Four years after leading
the Dallas Cowboys to one of their most memorable victories in team
history, backup quarterback Jason Garrett has been asked to be a
leading man again. But when Garrett takes the snap in the
nationally televised game against the New York Giants, he will not
be alone. His teammates and coaches vow they will not let the
32-year-old Ivy Leaguer shoulder all the responsibility. (Cantu,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DOLPHINS-MARINO _ DAVIE, Fla. _ Jimmy Johnson and Dan Marino
aren't buddies, and don't need to be. The difficulty is in the
adjustment of one man to the other. Johnson is, by title, the boss.
He's the head coach. Marino is, by reputation, the icon. He's the
superstar. Therein lies the potential for conflict, or, at least,
agitation. (Stoda, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   POWERBOAT-FOREMAN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ It's no accident that Roddy
Foreman is having his best year in power boat racing, capturing
another national championship recently. But an accident last year,
the most frightening one of his 17 years of racing, helped make his
current dream season possible. In the very first event last year,
his boat apparently hit something, suffered a puncture and then
went violently out of control. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED.
</P>
