<P>
   UNDATED _ It's time for baby boomers to divine what's going on
in the minds of the group of post-boomers now entering the
workplace _ the members of the so-called Generation X who are
beginning to put their own stamp on the world of work. To catch a
glimpse of the mindset of the youngest members of today's
workforce, read ``Rational Exuberance: The Influence of Generation
X on the New American Economy'' (The Penguin Group, $24.95, 274
pages). By TERESA McUSIC. Story has moved in ``f'' financial
category. &QL;
</P>
