<P>
   The Rev. J. Philip Wogaman, President Clinton's pastor, was
incorrectly identified as president of the board of the Interfaith
Alliance Foundation in an article about religious groups and
Clinton. Wogaman is president of the Interfaith Alliance, the
foundation's sister organization and its lobbying and
issues-advocacy arm.
</P>
