<P>
   ROACHES _ Do cockroaches fly? Not without a ticket. A Delta
flight was delayed Thursday when crew members found the plane was
infested with cockroaches. San Fransisco-bound passengers were
transferred to another jet after roaches were found in the first
plane's food-handling area. (Earle, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
6-8.
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS-HISTORY _ ATLANTA _ Athletes, officials, ACOG staff and
volunteers and myriad VIPs will assemble for two days this weekend
at the Atlanta History Center to record the first-ever oral history
of the Olympics. The recollections of real people, along with the
Olympic VIPs, will be videotaped for inclusion in the official
archives of the Games. (Turner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COKE _ The French government said Thursday it decided to block
Coca-Cola Co.'s (KO) proposed FRF5 billion acquisition of the
orange soft drink brand Orangina from drinks company Pernod Ricard
SA (F.PER), citing competition concerns. The decision comes as a
big surprise as most industry watchers had bet that the government
would give its green light to the pact despite the strenuous
objections of PepsiCo Inc. (PEP), which feared losing its
distribution channels in the French market as a result of the
agreement. (Gramig, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Moving in the (a) general news and (f) financial
categories.
