<P>
   TEXT ADVISORY
</P>
<P>
   At this hour, neither the timing nor the form of the release of
Clinton's grand jury testimony are certain. However, the New York
Times News Service will not move the full text.
</P>
<P>
   When it does become available, The Associated Press will make
the full text of the testimony through a password-required ftp site
and as an Adobe PDF file through AP Send. This is the same
procedure used by The AP for the full text of the Starr report last
week. See their advisories for additional information.
</P>
<P>
   The AP has also decided not to release the full text over normal
news wires.
</P>
