<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Friday, Sept. 18, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   LINDA-SMITH-CRITICIZE (Washington, D.C.) Washington Rep. Linda
Smith, fresh off her decisive victory in the GOP primary for U.S.
Senate, yesterday criticized Patty Murray's record on education,
defense, trade, ethanol subsidies, veteran's health care, and
sexual misconduct by public officials. In particular, Smith alleged
that Murray is so compromised in her support for free trade that
she has ignored the needs of several important Washington state
agricultural groups that are being hurt in international trade
disputes. The criticisms are contradicted not only by historical
documents but also by leaders of the apple and wheat industries
interviewed yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (story will move in the ``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Oakland) Ken Griffey Jr. hits a three-run homer _
his 53rd _ and Jamie Moyer pitches a complete game as the M's roll
8-0 at Oakland. Now it's off to Anaheim to play spoiler against the
division-leading Angels.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
