   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-SCANDAL (Washington) _ The House moves toward releasing
at least some of President Clinton' sexually explicit testimony in
the Monica Lewinsky investigation. Despite sharp divisions between
Republicans and Democrats, a compromise appears to be at hand that
would allow only portions of the four hours of taped testimony to
be made public. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
