investigate whether Clinton administration aides are orchestrating
a series of media reports revealing past adulterous affairs of
several Republican lawmakers. House Republican Whip Tom DeLay says
an attempt to intimidate members of Congress is against the law and
he names a key White House aide, Sidney Blumenthal, as the chief
suspect. By STEVE LASH.
