D-Calif., says she felt betrayed by President Clinton over the
Monica Lewinsky affair and said she rebuffed an offer to talk to
the president about it. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   LATE-ABORTION (Washington) _ In a victory for abortion rights
advocates, the Senate is expected to vote Friday to uphold
President Clinton's veto of legislation that would outlaw a
controversial late-term abortion procedure known by critics as
``partial-birth'' abortion. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already filed)
</P>
