   FBN-NFCEAST (Undated) _ With three of its teams winless and none
of the five above .500, the once-proud NFC East has degenerated
into the NFC Least so far this season. The division that ruled over
the NFL in the 1980s and early '90s appears to be worse than ever.
By JODY GOLDSTEIN.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UCLA (Undated) _ Under the guidance of former Texas A&AMP;M
assistant Bob Toledo, the UCLA football program has elevated itself
into the elite of college football. And the No.-5 ranked Bruins
have done it largely on the strength of a quick-striking, versatile
offense. By JERRY WIZIG.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-NORTHWESTERN (Undated) _ Three years ago, Northwestern was
the darling of college football as the long-dormant Wildcats rode a
dream season to the Rose Bowl. Now, coach Gary Barnett is trying to
put the pieces back together as Northwestern heads to Houston to
face Rice this weekend. By NEAL FARMER.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Houston) _ The impact of the Randy Johnson trade has
been felt in many ways for the Houston Astros. The team won 31 of
its next 40 games to vault into the upper echelon of baseball. The
franchise has drawn the five biggest crowds in team history since
Johnson's arrival. But the biggest impact has been on his
teammates, who have collectively lifted their game to a new level.
By JOSEPH DUARTE.
</P>
