</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-BRAVES-ONDECK18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On deck: Arizona Diamondbacks
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: Tonight and Saturday at 10:05 p.m.; Sunday at 4:05.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Bank One Ballpark.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: TBS, WSB 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: Tonight, RHP Greg Maddux (17-8,
2.15; first appearance vs. Diamondbacks) vs. RHP Andy Benes (13-13,
4.24; 4-12, 3.69 lifetime vs. Braves). Saturday, LHP Tom Glavine
(19-6, 2.63; 2-0, 1.29 lifetime vs. Diamondacks) vs. LHP Brian
Anderson (12-12, 4.34; 0-0, 9.00 lifetime vs. Braves). Sunday, LHP
Bruce Chen (1-0, 5.79; first appearance vs. Diamondbacks) vs. RHP
Amaury Telemaco (6-9, 3.92; 1-1, 3.29 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Quickly: This is an important game for Maddux, who was forced
from his last start after just six innings because of some
tightness in his upper right triceps. Although he brings a string
of 10 scoreless innings into the game, he will be watched closely
and will come out at the first hint of soreness. With a 5-6 record
in the second half, Maddux gets just this game and one more start
to impress the Cy Young electrorate. Once a shoo-in for his fifth
Cy Young, his fading candidacy needs a strong finish. The Braves
have beaten Benes in three different uniforms _ as a Padre, as a
Cardinal and on April 22 as a D-back. They catch the big
right-hander at his best stretch of the season. Benes is 6-2 in his
last nine starts and nearly threw his first no-hitter last time
out, when he yielded a one-out single in the ninth in Cincinnati on
Sunday. Take away a disastrous eight-run outing in New York on Aug.
22 and Benes has allowed only four runs in his last 40 innings,
striking out 35 while allowing 21 hits. He was 6-10 after his first
start of the second half but has gone 7-3 since. He went 0-1 in
back-to-back starts against Atlanta late in the season's first
month, giving up nine runs in 14 innings. Javy Lopez homered in
both of those games.
</P>
