NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 18
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-NLRB-DETROIT-PAPERS-NYT (moved on Tuesday, September 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, September
1, about a National Labor Relations Board ruling involving a
newspaper strike in Detroit misstated the former affiliation of
Benjamin J. Burns. He was executive editor of The Detroit News, not
The Detroit Free Press.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CANADA-BANKS-NYT (moved on Tuesday, September 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Sept. 15,
about the Manhattan District Attorney's prosecution of insider
trading cases referred incompletely to a New York court ruling on
state laws that apply. Besides endorsing prosecution under the
general business laws, which include the Martin Act, the court
found the penal law applicable.
</P>
</TEXT>
